{"parse":{"title":"toadstool","pageid":41414,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n\n===Alternative forms===\n* {{alter|en|toadestoole|todestoole||obsolete}}\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|tode-stole}}, {{m|enm|tadstol}}, {{m|enm|taddestol}}, equivalent to {{com|en|toad|stool}}. Compare dialectal {{cog|en|frogstool|t=toadstool}}, {{cog|stq|Poagestoul|t=mushroom|lit=frog's stool}}, {{cog|nl|paddenstoel}}.\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/ˈtəʊdˌstuːl/|a=UK}}\n* {{enPR|tōdʹsto͞ol'|a=US}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈtoʊdˌstu(ə)l/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-us-toadstool.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{rhymes|en|əʊdstuːl|oʊdstul|oʊdstuəl|s=2}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|subset of Q83093}} Any [[inedible]] or [[poisonous]] [[mushroom#English:_Q83093|mushroom]], especially an [[amanita]].\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en\n|toadstool disease\n|toadstool leather coral\n|toadstoollike\n}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|an inedible or poisonous mushroom}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t|bg|[[гъба]] (особено отровна)|f}}\n* Catalan: {{t|ca|bolet verinós}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|毒蕈|tr=dúxùn}}\n* Crimean Tatar: {{t|crh|ağuv mantar}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|muchomůrka|m}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|paddehat|c}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|giftige paddestoel|m}}, {{t|nl|gifzwam|m}}\n* Estonian: {{t+|et|mürkseen}}, {{t|et|mürgiseen}}, {{t|et|mürgine seen}}, {{t+|et|kärbseseen}} {{q|agaric, especially amanita}}\n* Faroese: {{t-needed|fo|}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|myrkkysieni}} {{q|poisonous mushroom}}, {{t+|fi|kärpässieni}} {{q|agaric}}, {{t|fi|roskasieni}} {{q|inedible}}\n* French: [[champignon]] [[vénéneux]] {{g|m}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Giftpilz}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|bolondgomba}}, {{t|hu|[[mérges]] [[gomba]]}}\n* Icelandic: {{t|is|körtukollur|m}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|beacán bearaigh|m}}\n* Italian: {{t|it|fungo velenoso}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|毒茸|tr=どくたけ, dokutake, どくきのこ, dokukinoko}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|독버섯}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|paddehatt|m}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|paddehatt|m}}\n* Pennsylvania German: {{t|pdc|Giftschwamm}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|muchomor|m}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|[[cogumelo]] [[venenoso]]|m}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|ciupercă otrăvitoare|f}}, {{qualifier|colloquial}} {{t|ro|ciupercă nebună|f}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|пога́нка|f}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|otrovna pečurka|f}}, Cyrillic: {{t|sh|отровна печурка|f}}\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|otrovna gljiva|f}}, Cyrillic: {{t|sh|отровна гљива|f}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|mušnica|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t|es|seta venenosa}}\n* Tagalog: {{t|tl|kabuting-ahas}}\n* Tamil: {{t+|ta|காளான்}}\n* Unami: {{t|unm|ahkokwe}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===See also===\n* {{l|en|fungus}}/[[fungi]]\n* {{l|en|mushroom}}\n\n{{C|en|Mushrooms}}"}}